              <p class="font-light text-stone-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                Dementia is more than just memory loss – it changes how a person thinks and communicates. To stay connected, you have to change too. Understanding how brain change affects your loved one will help you learn what to say and, more importantly, what not to say.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-500">
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  All Caregivers
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Card>

          <Card>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">Caring for the Alzheimer's Caregiver</h3>
              <p class="font-light text-stone-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                Address caregiver burnout, emotional resilience, and the unique challenges of supporting those who care for individuals with dementia.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-500">
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Professional Caregivers
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Card>

          <Card>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">Doing the Wrong Things for the Right Reasons – Maybe There's a Better Way?</h3>
              <p class="font-light text-stone-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                Examine common caregiving approaches that, despite good intentions, may not serve the person with dementia. Learn evidence-based alternatives that truly help.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-500">
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  All Caregivers
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Card>

          <Card>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">Could This Be Alzheimer's? Recognizing Early Warning Signs of Memory Loss</h3>
              <p class="font-light text-stone-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                Learn to distinguish between normal aging and concerning signs of cognitive decline. Understand when to seek evaluation and what to expect from the diagnostic process.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-500">
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Churches & Communities
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Card>

          <Card>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">FAQs about Dementia</h3>
              <p class="font-light text-stone-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                Get answers to the most common questions about dementia, from diagnosis and progression to practical caregiving strategies and available resources.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-500">
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Churches & Communities
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Card>

          <Card>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">Learning to Dance with Dementia – How Changing Your Approach Changes the Outcome</h3>
              <p class="font-light text-stone-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                Discover how flexibility and person-centered approaches create positive interactions. Learn to adapt your caregiving style to meet changing needs.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-500">
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  All Caregivers
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Card>

          <Card>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">Living Next Door to Dementia</h3>
              <p class="font-light text-stone-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                Whether you call it dementia, or Alzheimer's, or memory loss, the result is the same: it's a disease that changes everything. With our growing aging population, and without a cure anywhere on the horizon, we are called to learn all we can about a condition that will likely affect at least 50% of us. Join us for this interactive program to explore the differences between normal and not normal aging, how to recognize common early signs of dementia, and what you can do to support families in your community who are already affected by this condition.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-500">
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Minimum 4 hours
                </p>
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Churches & Communities
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Card>

          <Card>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">Less Talk, More Smiles – Adopting a Positive Approach to Dementia in Long-Term Care</h3>
              <p class="font-light text-stone-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                Transform your facility's culture with practical strategies for person-centered care that prioritize connection over correction and understanding over instruction.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-500">
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Professional Caregivers & Facility Staff
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Card>

          <Card>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">What Part of "No!" Don't You Understand?</h3>
              <p class="font-light text-stone-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                Explore the reasons behind resistance and refusal in dementia care. Learn strategies to work with, rather than against, these challenging moments.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-500">
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z" />
                  </svg>
                  Professional Caregivers
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Card>

          <Card>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">Diamonds to Pearls – Using Teepa's GEMS to Identify the Progression of Dementia</h3>
              <p class="font-light text-stone-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                Learn Teepa Snow's GEMS framework for understanding dementia progression and how to adapt care approaches as abilities change throughout the journey.
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-500">
                <p class="flex items-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
